<div class=3DWordSection1>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
roops
defend your colonies against invasion by enemy empires. They can also be us=
ed
as attacking forces to invade and take over enemy colonies.<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Strength and Readi=
ness<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>E=
ach race
has a natural strength for its troops. This strength is determined by the r=
aces
aggression and intelligence levels &#8211; more aggressive and intelligent
races will produce stronger troops.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
he
readiness of troops for combat is measured on a scale from 1 to 100. Troops=
 at
a readiness level of 100 are completely rested and ready for battle. When
troops are in combat they suffer losses and their readiness drops. Readiness
takes time to rise back to 100. Medical facilities can accelerate healing of
troop readiness.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

