</span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><sp=
an
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Special Forces</span></b><sp=
an
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>: excel at destroying enemy
defensive facilities (fortified bunkers, planetary shields, etc) and destro=
ying
defending Planetary <span class=3DSpellE>Defense</span> units. Defending Sp=
ecial
Forces focus on eliminating invading Special Forces units.<o:p></o:p></span=
></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_1" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1028"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:354.6pt;margin=
-top:0;
 width:405.8pt;height:115pt;z-index:251658752;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:page;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_Troops_files/image009.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D541 height=3D153
src=3D"GameConcepts_Troops_files/image005.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_1"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Each troop type has separate=
 Attack
and <span class=3DSpellE>Defense</span> strength values. Some troop types a=
re
also larger than normal, and thus take more space on troop transport ships.
Each troop type also has different maintenance <span class=3DGramE>costs,</=
span>
e.g. <span class=3DSpellE>Armored</span> troops are more expensive to maint=
ain
than Infantry.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>N=
ote that
research is needed to recruit troop types other than Infantry. The <span
class=3DSpellE>Armored</span> Factory planetary facility is needed to recru=
it <span
class=3DSpellE>Armored</span> troops at a colony. The Military Academy plan=
etary
facility is needed to recruit Special Forces troops at a colony.<o:p></o:p>=
</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
he Troops
section of the Weapons tech tree on the Research screen (F7) has a number of
upgrades for each troop type. Hover over each research project to see detai=
ls
of each upgrade.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Troop Loadouts for=
 Ships
and Fleets<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_4" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1027"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:155.8pt;margin=
-top:0;
 width:207pt;height:93.5pt;z-index:251659776;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:page;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_Troops_files/image011.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D276 height=3D125
src=3D"GameConcepts_Troops_files/image006.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_4"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>You can specify the preferred
loadout of each troop type for both individual troop transport ships and for
fleets. This can simplify the automated loading of troops onto troop
transports.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>F=
or single
ships you specify the troop loadout in the Troops tab of the Ships and Bases
screen (F11). You can alter the amounts for each troop type that a ship sho=
uld
load when picking up troops. The total size of the troop loadout cannot exc=
eed
the troop capacity of the ship. If the ship is part of a fleet then the
fleet&#8217;s troop loadout overrides the ship&#8217;s troop loadout.<o:p><=
/o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>F=
or fleets you
specify the troop loadout in the Fleets screen (F12). You specify the
percentages for each troop type that a fleet should load when picking up
troops. The actual amounts of each troop type change as ships are added and
removed from the fleet, thus changing the troop capacity of the fleet.<o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>N=
ote that
even though you can specify a preferred troop loadout for a ship or fleet, =
in
practice other factors can alter which troops are actually picked up. There=
 may
not be sufficient ungarrisoned troops of the requested type available for
pickup at your colonies. When there are insufficient troops of a specified =
type
to meet the preferred troop loadout, then the ship or fleet will attempt to
substitute other troop types to completely fill the ship or fleet.<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Balance and planni=
ng<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>B=
e careful
not to recruit too many troops &#8211; the maintenance costs can put a large
drain on your funds.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_8" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:171.35pt;margi=
n-top:0;
 width:222.55pt;height:113.35pt;z-index:251656704;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_Troops_files/image003.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D297 height=3D151
src=3D"GameConcepts_Troops_files/image007.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_8"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Thus when you are at peace w=
ith your
<span class=3DSpellE>neighbors</span>, minimize spending by keeping only th=
e bare
minimum of troops on your key colonies. When you decide to go on the offens=
ive
against another empire, recruit more troops.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Transporting your =
Troops<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
roops can
be loaded onto ships that have troop storage components, such as troop
transports or larger military ships. They can then be sent to another colony
and unloaded there to reinforce it. Or they can be used as an invasion forc=
e at
an enemy colony.</span></p>

</div>

</body>

</html>

